2015-11-04  Andreas Leibl  <andreas@leibl.co.uk>

	* certnanny: release version 1.2.0

	* Improved debugging

	* Removed carriage returns on all files that aren't specifically Windows

	* Code and comment cleanup

	* Multiple bugfixes

	* New options: cfgdump and datadump

	* New option --force to force renewal (for debugging)

2015-05-11  Martin Bartosch  <m.bartosch@cynops.de>

	* Solaris and AIX packing improvements

	* certnanny: release version 1.1.3

	* MQ keystore support: fix for detecting labels on Windows systems

2014-02-28  Martin Bartosch  <m.bartosch@cynops.de>

	* certnanny: release version 1.1

	* improved configuration features

	* support of different key sizes in keystores

	* Root CA certificates now stored in directory

	* fully automatic Root CA update feature via SCEP GetNextCA

	* "Root Only" Keystores (for trust anchor configuration)

	* improved Windows keystore support (Machine Keystore)

	* updated GSKit 7.1 support

	* meta data submission in SCEP request

	* additional hook functions (expired, invocation)

	* improved logging

	* packaging for all major platforms

2007-06-19  Martin Bartosch  <m.bartosch@cynops.de>

	* certnanny: release version 0.10
	
	* certnanny: added policy configuration option to allow for 
	explicit inclusion or exclusion of expired/not yet valid 
	root certificates

	* certnanny: by default expired root certificates are no longer 
	imported into newly created keystores

	* certnanny: added PKCS#12 support

	* certnanny: added GSKit keystore support on the Windows 
	platform fixed several platform issues (Windows platform 
	needs binmode most of the time)

2006-08-09  Martin Bartosch  <m.bartosch@cynops.de>

	* certnanny: fixed incorrect chaining semantics (only causes problems
	if issuing CA rollover happened)

2006-08-02  Martin Bartosch  <m.bartosch@cynops.de>

	* certnanny: completely rewrote CA certificate chaining function

2006-06-07  Joerg Schneider <js@joergschneider.com>

	* certnanny: release version 0.8

2006-05-17  Thomas Thiele <thomas.thiele@db.com>

	* certnanny: Windows Certifcate Store support
	
2006-05-05  Joerg Schneider <js@joergschneider.com>

	* certnanny: added support for OpenSSL 0.9.8

	* certnanny: fixed a bug that the warnexpiry hook would be called when
	  a certificate is valid for less than autorenew_days days. Now the
	  warnexpiry hook is _only_ called when a certificate is valid for less
	  than warnexpiry_days.

	* certnanny: OpenSSL keystore: fixed a wrong default value for keytype
	  (PKCS8) introduced in 0.7. Correct default value: OpenSSL

	* certnanny: improved log format and made all (non-fatal error)
	  messages honor the loglevel. Introduced loglevel 5 (debug scep).

	* certnanny: added new option scepchecksubjectname, which activates a
	  subject name check (-C) supported by newer sscep versions
	
	* certnanny: --help print version number

	* certnanny: README and manual page create with pod2text/pod2man from
	  make

2006-04-20  Joerg Schneider <js@joergschneider.com>

	* certnanny: added Java keystore support

